                            <comment id="14466551" author="chanwit" created="Fri, 27 Feb 2009 07:40:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve tried to groovyc the following B.groovy (same as the testcase):&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;interface&lt;/span&gt; B {
   &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Class&lt;/span&gt; type = B.class
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The result are 2 classes, B.class and another B$1.class, which seems to be an inner class of B caused by the above declaration.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14466559" author="roshandawrani" created="Fri, 27 Feb 2009 21:45:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Class expressions used in interface(ClassNode) were being stored in its helper inner class (InnerClassNode) as synthetic fields but were being accessed as synthetic getters. Resolved by accessing them as fields instead.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Fixed on 1.6.1 and trunk.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
